{"title_page": "USCV-3", "text_new": "{{short description|United States Commercial Vehicle mission 1, aboard SpaceX Dragon-2}}\n{{Use American English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox spaceflight\n| name = US Crew Vehicle-3\n| image = SpaceX Crew Dragon (More cropped).jpg\n| image_caption = \n| insignia = \n| mission_type = Crewed mission to ISS\n| operator = [[NASA]]/[[SpaceX]]\n| COSPAR_ID = \n| SATCAT = \n| mission_duration = ~210 days <ref>https://www.nasa.gov/specials/dm2/</ref>\n| distance_travelled = \n| orbits_completed = \n| spacecraft = \n| spacecraft_type = [[Crew Dragon]]\n| manufacturer = [[SpaceX]]\n| launch_mass = {{convert|NNNN| | |abbr=on}}\n| landing_mass = {{convert|NNNN| | |abbr=on}}\n| launch_date = NET 2021\n| launch_rocket = [[Falcon 9 Full Thrust#Block 5|Falcon 9]]\n| launch_site = [[Kennedy Space Center]], [[Launch Complex 39|LC-39A]]\n| launch_contractor = [[SpaceX]]\n| landing_date = NET 2021\n| landing_site = [[Atlantic Ocean]]\n| crew_size = 4\n| crew_members = [[Kjell Lindgren]] <br> TBA <br> [[Matthias Maurer]] <br> [[Andrei Borisenko]]\n| crew_callsign = \n| crew_photo = \n| crew_photo_caption = \n| docking = {{Infobox spaceflight/Dock\n| docking_target   = [[International Space Station|ISS]]\n| docking_type     = Dock\n| docking_port     = \n| docking_date     = \n| undocking_date   = \n| time_docked      = Six months (planned)\n}}\n| orbit_epoch = \n| orbit_reference = [[geocentric orbit|Geocentric]]\n| orbit_regime = [[Low Earth orbit|Low Earth]]\n| orbit_periapsis = \n| orbit_apoapsis = \n| orbit_inclination = 51.6\u00b0\n| orbit_period = \n| apsis = gee\n| programme = [[Commercial Crew Development|Commercial Crew Program]]\n| previous_mission = [[USCV-2]]\n| next_mission = [[USCV-4]]\n| programme2 = [[Crew Dragon]] crewed flights\n| previous_mission2 = [[USCV-1]]\n| next_mission2 = [[USCV-5]]\n}}\n\n'''USCV-3''' (US Crew Vehicle-3), also known as '''SpaceX Crew Dragon-2''' , will be a [[SpaceX]] [[Crew Dragon]] spaceflight scheduled to ferry four astronauts to the [[International Space Station]] for an approximately six month stay on the laboratory. \n\n== Crew ==\nUSCV-3 will most likly be commanded by [[USCV-1]] backup commander [[Kjell Lindgren]], joined by a second NASA astronaut and German [[European Space Agency]] astronaut [[Matthias Maurer]], who is in line to fly following fellow ESA astronaut [[Thomas Pesquet]] according to ESA director-general [[Johann-Dietrich W\u00f6rner]]<ref>https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2019/10/one-on-one-esa-johann-dietrich-worner/</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/ShuttleAlmanac/status/1254937803667853313/photo/1</ref>. [[Roscosmos]] has confirmed they want each Commercial Crew Vehicle to be more certified before they assign a Russian cosmonaut to fly either vehicle, therefore USCV-3 will most likely be the first USCV flight to carry a Russian crew member, currently [[Andrei Borisenko]] is slated to be the first cosmonaut to fly aboard a commercial vehicle<ref>https://ria.ru/20200306/1568224012.html</ref>.\n\n{{Spaceflight crew\n|terminology    = Astronaut\n\n|position1      = Spacecraft commander\n|crew1_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Kjell Lindgren]]\n|flights1_up    = Second\n|agency1_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition1_up = Expedition TBA\n\n|position2      = Joint operations commander\n|crew2_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} TBA\n|flights2_up    = TBA\n|agency2_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition2_up = Expedition TBA\n|position3      = Mission Specialist 1\n|crew3_up       = {{Flagicon|GER}} [[Matthias Maurer]]\n|flights3_up    = First\n|agency3_up     = [[ESA]]\n|expedition3_up = Expedition TBA\n\n|position4      = Mission Specialist 2\n|crew4_up       = {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Andrei Borisenko]]\n|flights4_up    = Third\n|agency4_up     = [[Roscosmos|RKA]]\n|expedition4_up = Expedition TBA\n}}\n\n===Back-up crew===\n{{Spaceflight crew\n|terminology    = Astronaut\n|references     = <ref>http://www.gctc.ru/main.php?id=4568</ref>\n\n|position1      = Spacecraft commander\n|crew1_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} TBA\n|flights1_up    = Second\n|agency1_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition1_up = \n\n|position2      = Joint operations commander\n|crew2_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} TBA\n|flights2_up    = TBA\n|agency2_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition2_up = \n\n|position3      = Mission Specialist 1\n|crew3_up       = TBA\n|flights3_up    = TBA\n|agency3_up     = \n|expedition3_up = \n\n|position4      = Mission Specialist 2\n|crew4_up       = {{Flagicon|RUS}} TBA\n|flights4_up    = TBA\n|agency4_up     = \n|expedition4_up = \n}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Boeing CST-100 Starliner]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Portal|Spaceflight}}\n{{Manned ISS flights}}\n{{Dragon spaceflights}}\n{{Falcon rocket launches}}\n{{Future spaceflights}}\n\n[[Category:Dragon 2]]\n[[Category:SpaceX payloads contracted by NASA]]\n[[Category:SpaceX human spaceflights]]\n[[Category:Future human spaceflights]]\n\n\n{{space-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|United States Commercial Vehicle mission 1, aboard SpaceX Dragon-2}}\n{{Use American English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox spaceflight\n| name = US Crew Vehicle-3\n| image = SpaceX Crew Dragon (More cropped).jpg\n| image_caption = \n| insignia = \n| mission_type = Crewed mission to ISS\n| operator = [[NASA]]/[[SpaceX]]\n| COSPAR_ID = \n| SATCAT = \n| mission_duration = ~210 days <ref>https://www.nasa.gov/specials/dm2/</ref>\n| distance_travelled = \n| orbits_completed = \n| spacecraft = \n| spacecraft_type = [[Crew Dragon]]\n| manufacturer = [[SpaceX]]\n| launch_mass = {{convert|NNNN| | |abbr=on}}\n| landing_mass = {{convert|NNNN| | |abbr=on}}\n| launch_date = NET 2021\n| launch_rocket = [[Falcon 9 Full Thrust#Block 5|Falcon 9]]\n| launch_site = [[Kennedy Space Center]], [[Launch Complex 39|LC-39A]]\n| launch_contractor = [[SpaceX]]\n| landing_date = NET 2021\n| landing_site = [[Atlantic Ocean]]\n| crew_size = 4\n| crew_members = [[Kjell Lindgren]] <br> TBA <br> [[Matthias Maurer]] <br> [[Andrei Borisenko]]\n| crew_callsign = \n| crew_photo = \n| crew_photo_caption = \n| docking = {{Infobox spaceflight/Dock\n| docking_target   = [[International Space Station|ISS]]\n| docking_type     = Dock\n| docking_port     = \n| docking_date     = \n| undocking_date   = \n| time_docked      = Six months (planned)\n}}\n| orbit_epoch = \n| orbit_reference = [[geocentric orbit|Geocentric]]\n| orbit_regime = [[Low Earth orbit|Low Earth]]\n| orbit_periapsis = \n| orbit_apoapsis = \n| orbit_inclination = 51.6\u00b0\n| orbit_period = \n| apsis = gee\n| programme = [[Commercial Crew Development|Commercial Crew Program]]\n| previous_mission = [[USCV-2]]\n| next_mission = [[USCV-4]]\n| programme2 = [[Crew Dragon]] crewed flights\n| previous_mission2 = [[USCV-1]]\n| next_mission2 = [[USCV-5]]\n}}\n\n'''USCV-3''' (US Crew Vehicle-3), also known as '''SpaceX Crew Dragon-2''' , will be a [[SpaceX]] [[Crew Dragon]] spaceflight scheduled to ferry four astronauts to the [[International Space Station]] for an approximately six month stay on the laboratory. \n\n== Crew ==\nUSCV-3 will most likly be commanded by [[USCV-1]] backup commander [[Kjell Lindgren]], joined by a second NASA astronaut and German [[European Space Agency]] astronaut [[Matthias Maurer]], who is in line to fly following fellow ESA astronaut [[Thomas Pesquet]] according to ESA director-general [[Johann-Dietrich W\u00f6rner]]<ref>https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2019/10/one-on-one-esa-johann-dietrich-worner/</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/ShuttleAlmanac/status/1254937803667853313/photo/1</ref>. [[Roscosmos]] has confirmed they want each Commercial Crew Vehicle to be more certified before they assign a Russian cosmonaut to fly either vehicle, therefore USCV-3 will most likely be the first USCV flight to carry a Russian crew member, currently [[Andrei Borisenko]] is slated to be the first cosmonaut to fly aboard a commercial vehicle<ref>https://ria.ru/20200306/1568224012.html</ref>.\n\n{{Spaceflight crew\n|terminology    = Astronaut\n\n|position1      = Spacecraft commander\n|crew1_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} [[Kjell Lindgren]]\n|flights1_up    = Second\n|agency1_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition1_up = TBA\n\n|position2      = Joint operations commander\n|crew2_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} TBA\n|flights2_up    = TBA\n|agency2_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition2_up = TBA\n|position3      = Mission Specialist 1\n|crew3_up       = {{Flagicon|GER}} [[Matthias Maurer]]\n|flights3_up    = First\n|agency3_up     = [[ESA]]\n|expedition3_up = TBA\n\n|position4      = Mission Specialist 2\n|crew4_up       = {{Flagicon|RUS}} [[Andrei Borisenko]]\n|flights4_up    = Third\n|agency4_up     = [[Roscosmos|RKA]]\n|expedition4_up = TBA\n}}\n\n===Back-up crew===\n{{Spaceflight crew\n|terminology    = Astronaut\n|references     = <ref>http://www.gctc.ru/main.php?id=4568</ref>\n\n|position1      = Spacecraft commander\n|crew1_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} TBA\n|flights1_up    = Second\n|agency1_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition1_up = \n\n|position2      = Joint operations commander\n|crew2_up       = {{Flagicon|USA}} TBA\n|flights2_up    = TBA\n|agency2_up     = [[NASA]]\n|expedition2_up = \n\n|position3      = Mission Specialist 1\n|crew3_up       = TBA\n|flights3_up    = TBA\n|agency3_up     = \n|expedition3_up = \n\n|position4      = Mission Specialist 2\n|crew4_up       = {{Flagicon|RUS}} TBA\n|flights4_up    = TBA\n|agency4_up     = \n|expedition4_up = \n}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Boeing CST-100 Starliner]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Portal|Spaceflight}}\n{{Manned ISS flights}}\n{{Dragon spaceflights}}\n{{Falcon rocket launches}}\n{{Future spaceflights}}\n\n[[Category:Dragon 2]]\n[[Category:SpaceX payloads contracted by NASA]]\n[[Category:SpaceX human spaceflights]]\n[[Category:Future human spaceflights]]\n\n\n{{space-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Toby6250", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCrew", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USCV-3"}
{"title_page": "Jason Momoa", "text_new": "{{short description|American actor and model born in Hawaii}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jasper Anthony Marcus Nukos\n| image              = Jason Momoa by Gage Skidmore 2.jpg\n| alt                = \n| caption            = Momoa in 2018\n| birth_name         = Joseph Jason Namakaeha Momoa\n| height             = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1979|8|1}}\n| birth_place        = [[N\u0101n\u0101kuli, Hawaii|N\u0101n\u0101kuli]], [[Honolulu]], [[Hawaii]], U.S.\n| residence          = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| occupation         = {{Hlist|Actor|model}}\n| years_active       = 1992\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{Marriage|[[Lisa Bonet]]|2017}}\n| children           = 2\n| relatives          = [[Zo\u00eb Kravitz]] (stepdaughter);\n [[Finn Clarke]] (father).\n| signature          = Jason Momoa autograph.png\n}}\n\n'''Joseph Jason Namakaeha Momoa'''<ref name=desmoinesregister /> (born August 1, 1979)<ref name=desmoinesregister /> is \nan American actor, best known for playing [[Khal Drogo]] in the [[HBO]] [[fantasy]] television series ''[[Game of Thrones|Encantadia]]'', [[Ronon Dex]] in ''[[Stargate Atlantis]], ''Declan Harp in the [[Canadian]] series ''[[Frontier (2016 TV series)|Frontier]]'', and [[Aquaman]] in the [[DC Extended Universe]] films ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'', ''[[Justice League (film)|Justice League]]'', and ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nAn only child, Momoa was born in 1979 in [[N\u0101n\u0101kuli, Hawaii|N\u0101n\u0101kuli]], [[Honolulu]],\n[[Hawaii]]<ref name=\"Jason Momoa Interview\">{{cite news |url=https://www.staradvertiser.com/2018/12/16/hawaii-news/hawaii-born-actor-jason-momoas-role-in-aquaman-parallels-his-own-upbringing/ |title=Hawaii-born actor Jason Momoa's 'Aquaman' role parallels own upbringing |work=Star Advertiser |date=December 16, 2018 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> to Coni (Lemke), a photographer and Joseph Momoa, a painter.<ref name=desmoinesregister>{{cite news |first=Sophia |last=Ahmad |url=http://blogs.desmoinesregister.com/dmr/index.php/2010/02/19/interview-with-norwalk-conan-star-jason-momoa |title=Interview with Norwalk\u2019s \u2018Conan\u2019 star Jason Momoa |work=[[Des Moines Register]]|location=Iowa|date=February 19, 2010 |access-date=February 23, 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130408022415/http://blogs.desmoinesregister.com/dmr/index.php/2010/02/19/interview-with-norwalk-conan-star-jason-momoa |archive-date=April 8, 2013}}</ref> He was raised in [[Norwalk, Iowa]], by his mother.<ref name=\"Jason Momoa Interview\" /> His father is of [[Native Hawaiian]] ancestry<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.factinate.com/people/42-imposing-facts-jason-momoa/ |title=42 Imposing Facts About Jason Momoa |date=August 9, 2018 |first=Cadeem |last=Lalor |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Jason Momoa Interview\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.peoplesworld.org/article/aquaman-the-life-aquatic-with-hawaiian-polynesian-power-superhero-jason-momoa/ |title='Aquaman': The life aquatic with Hawaiian Polynesian Power superhero Jason Momoa |work=Peoples World |date=January 3, 2019 |first=Ed |last=Rampell |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> and his mother is of [[Germans|German]], [[Irish people|Irish]], and [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] descent.<ref name=\"Jason Momoa Interview\" /> After high school, Momoa attended college and initially majored in [[marine biology]] before switching to [[wildlife biology]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/redeye/ct-redeye-xpm-2014-03-04-47905420-story.html |title=Jason Momoa takes 'The Red Road' |first=Curt |last=Wagner |date=March 4, 2014 |work=The Chicago Tribune |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Jason momoa.jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|Momoa during the filming of ''Stargate Atlantis'' in 2006]]\nIn 1998, Momoa was discovered by designer Eric Chandler and Takeo Kobayashi,<ref>{{cite web |title=Takeo Kobayashi |url=http://www.midweek.com/takeo-kobayashi/ |website=Midweek.com |date=December 19, 2012 |first=Chris |last=Fleck |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> who encouraged his [[Model (person)|modeling career]].  At 19 years old, he also worked part-time in a surf shop before being cast in the [[Action (genre)|action]] [[Dramatic programming|drama series]] ''[[Baywatch Hawaii]]'',<ref name=\"katiecouric1\">{{cite web |url=http://katiecouric.com/videos/game-of-thrones-jason-momoa/ |title=\"Game of Thrones\" Star Jason Momoa |publisher=KatieCouric.com |access-date=February 23, 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140904033741/http://katiecouric.com/videos/game-of-thrones-jason-momoa/ |archive-date=September 4, 2014}}</ref> where he appeared as [[Jason Ioane]] (1999\u20132001).<ref>{{cite web |last=Kelly |first=Helen |url=https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/667229/Game-of-Thrones-Jason-Momoa-Khal-Drogo-Baywatch-Hawaii-Model |title=Game of Thrones: Jason Momoa is unrecognisable as young model before Khal Drogo role |work=Daily Express |date=May 5, 2016 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to his appearances in ''[[North Shore (TV series)|North Shore]]'' (2004\u20132005), ''[[Johnson Family Vacation]]'' (2004), and ''[[Stargate: Atlantis]]'' (2005\u20132009), Momoa was cast as Roman in four episodes of the [[comedy-drama]] television series ''[[The Game (U.S. TV series)|The Game]]'' (2009). He portrayed the title protagonist in ''[[Conan the Barbarian (2011 film)|Conan the Barbarian]]'' (2011), a [[remake|reimagining]] of the 1982 film of the same name and a role made famous by [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]]. Momoa gained his role of [[Khal Drogo]] on HBO's ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' through his audition, in which he performed a [[Haka]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://time.com/4641078/game-of-thrones-jason-momoa-khal-drogo-audition/ |title=''Game of Thrones''<nowiki>'</nowiki> Jason Momoa Tells the Origin Story Behind His Viral Audition |website=Time.com |date=January 20, 2017 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> one of many intimidating [[M\u0101ori culture|M\u0101ori]] dances traditionally used to convey a challenge to an opponent, or a welcome to a visitor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maori.org.nz/waiata/default.php?pid=sp95&parent=85|title=Kapa Haka|last=|first=|date=1996|work=maori.org.nz/|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMomoa directed and co-wrote ''[[Road to Paloma]]'' (2014), an American [[drama]] [[thriller film]], together with writers Jonathan Hirschbein and Robert Homer Mollohan. The film stars Momoa, [[Sarah Shahi]], [[Lisa Bonet]], [[Michael Raymond-James]], and [[Wes Studi]].<ref name=\"collider\">{{cite web |title=Exclusive: Jason Momoa Talks CONAN; Reveals He's Writing and Directing ROAD TO PALOMA |url=http://collider.com/jason-momoa-conan-road-to-paloma-interview/ |publisher=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> It premiered at the [[Sarasota Film Festival|2014 Sarasota Film Festival]] in April 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/jason-momoas-road-to-paloma-to-premiere-in-2014-sarasota-film-festival-1201130089/ |title=Jason Momoa's 'Road to Paloma' to Premiere at Sarasota Film Festival |work=Variety |date=March 12, 2014 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> The film had a limited theatrical release on July 15, 2014 in [[New York City]] and [[Los Angeles]] and a VOD release.<ref>{{cite web |last=Schwartz |first=Terri |url=http://blog.zap2it.com/pop2it/2014/02/jason-momoa-landed-the-red-road-thanks-to-his-directorial-debut-road-to-paloma.html |title=Jason Momoa landed 'The Red Road' thanks to his directorial debut 'Road to Paloma' |work=Blog.zap2it.com |date=February 26, 2014 |access-date=February 23, 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302181100/http://blog.zap2it.com/pop2it/2014/02/jason-momoa-landed-the-red-road-thanks-to-his-directorial-debut-road-to-paloma.html |archive-date=March 2, 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Jason Momoa Supercon 2014.jpg|left|thumb|upright|Momoa in 2014]]\nIn March 2014, Momoa joined the dark comedy/thriller indie ''[[Sugar Mountain (film)|Sugar Mountain]]'' alongside [[Cary Elwes]] and [[Haley Webb]]; its principal photography was done in Alaska.<ref name=\"sugarmountain\">{{cite web |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/115943-cary-elwes-and-jason-momoa-to-climb-sugar-mountain |title=Cary Elwes and Jason Momoa to Climb Sugar Mountain |publisher=ComingSoon.net |date=March 12, 2014 |first=Silas |last=Lesnick |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cary-elwes-jason-momoa-join-indie-sugar-mountain-688082 |title=Cary Elwes, Jason Momoa Join Indie 'Sugar Mountain' |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=March 12, 2014 |first=Rebecca |last=Ford |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> He also starred as Phillip Kopus, a [[Ramapough Mountain Indians|Ramapough Mountain Indian]], on the [[SundanceTV]] drama series ''[[The Red Road (TV series)|The Red Road]]'' (2014\u20132015).<ref name=\"redroad\">{{cite web |url=http://seriable.com/the-red-road-cancelled-by-sundancetv-after-two-seasons/ |website=Seriable.com |title=The Red Road Cancelled By SundanceTV After Two Seasons |date=May 23, 2015 |access-date=February 23, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826135115/http://seriable.com/the-red-road-cancelled-by-sundancetv-after-two-seasons/ |archive-date=August 26, 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2014, Momoa was reported to have been cast in the role of [[Aquaman]]. He first played the role in a cameo in the superhero film ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'',<ref name=\"JasonMomoaAquaman\">{{cite news |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/aquaman-jason-momoa-batman-v-superman-dawn-of-justice/ |title=Jason Momoa Is Aquaman in 'Batman V Superman: Dawn Of Justice' |access-date=February 23, 2019 |newspaper=[[/Film]] |date=June 14, 2014 |first=Peter |last=Sciretta}}</ref><ref name=\"JasonMomoaAquaman2\">{{cite web |url=https://uproxx.com/hitfix/jason-momoa-will-play-aquaman-in-dawn-of-justice-and-we-know-how-it-will-happen/ |title=Jason Momoa Will Play Aquaman in 'Dawn of Justice', and We Know how It Will Happen |last=McWeeny |first=Drew |work=Hitfix |date=June 14, 2014 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"JasonMomoaAquaman3\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jason-momoa-playing-aquaman-batman-711899 |title=Jason Momoa to Play Aquaman in 'Batman v. Superman: Dawn of Justice' |first1=Rebecca |last1=Ford |first2=Borys |last2=Kit |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=June 16, 2014 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> marking Aquaman's live action theatrical debut. Momoa played the character in a leading role in the 2017 [[ensemble film]] ''[[Justice League (film)|Justice League]]''. He then starred in the ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]'' solo film, which released in late 2018.<ref name=\"aquabat\">{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/aquaman-movie-actor-jason-momoa-official/ |title=It's Official: Jason Momoa is 'Aquaman'; Solo Movie Coming 2018 |date=October 15, 2014 |work=Screen Rant |access-date=February 23, 2019 |first=Andrew |last=Dice}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/dc-movie-slate-revealed/ |title=DC Comics Movies Announced: 'Suicide Squad,' 'Wonder Woman,' 'Justice League,' 'The Flash,' 'Aquaman' |work=Slashfilm |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"V-Aquaman\">{{cite web |first=Justin |last=Kroll |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/aquaman-james-wan-directing-1201511748/ |title=James Wan to Direct 'Aquaman' for Warner Bros. |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=June 3, 2015 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> He also reprised this role in ''[[The LEGO Movie 2: The Second Part]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.avclub.com/jason-momoas-aquaman-will-splash-around-in-the-lego-mov-1831379994 |title=Jason Momoa's Aquaman will splash around in ''The Lego Movie 2'' |first=William |last=Hughes |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Momoa portrayed Connor in the Canadian horror action film ''[[Wolves (2014 film)|Wolves]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/91414/uk-exclusive-wolves-gag-reel-serves-howlers/ |title=UK Exclusive: Wolves Gag Reel Serves Up a Few Howlers |first=Gareth |last=Jones |date=February 28, 2015 |work=DreadCentral.com |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> and starred in the Sci-fi horror movie ''[[Debug (film)|Debug]];'' it was written and directed by Momoa's former ''Stargate Atlantis'' co-star, British-born Canadian actor [[David Hewlett]]. In February 2015, it was announced that he would portray a [[Cannibalism|cannibal]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/89009/jason-momoa-eats-bad-batch-human-flesh/ |title=Jason Momoa Eats a Bad Batch of Human Flesh |first=Steve |last=Barton |website=DreadCentral.com |date=February 6, 2015 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> in the drama thriller film ''The Bad Batch''.<ref name=\"thebadbatch\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/jason-momoa-in-talks-to-star-in-cannibal-love-story-the-bad-batch-for-annapurna-vice-exclusive/ |title=Jason Momoa in Talks to Star in Cannibal Love Story 'The Bad Batch' for Annapurna, Vice (Exclusive) |first=Jeff |last=Sneider |date=February 6, 2015 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> In 2015, Momoa was cast in the Canadian action film ''[[Braven]]'', which was released on February 2, 2018.\n\nIn early 2017, he signed onto the official ''Just Cause'' movie series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/jason-momoa-just-cause-movie-1202003798/ |title='Aquaman's' Jason Momoa to Star in 'Just Cause' Film Adaptation |first=Dave |last=McNary |date=March 7, 2017 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/entertainment/2017/03/jason-momoa-lands-just-cause-movie-lead.html |title=Jason Momoa lands Just Cause movie lead |date=August 3, 2017 |website=newshub.co.nz |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2018, Momoa was cast for Apple's upcoming future-based drama series [[See (TV series)|''See'']].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/jason-momoa-star-apple-drama-see-1126050 |title=Jason Momoa to Star in Apple Drama 'See' |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=July 10, 2018 |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/jason-momoa-apple-see-1202869906/ |title=Jason Momoa to Star in Apple Sci-Fi Series 'See' |last=Otterson |first=Joe |date=July 10, 2018 |work=Variety |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2019, Momoa was cast as [[Duncan Idaho]] in the upcoming [[Denis Villeneuve]] film ''[[Dune (2020 film)|Dune]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/jason-momoa-dune-aquaman-frank-herbert-denis-villenueve-1202557876/ |title='Aquaman's Jason Momoa Joins Killer Cast Of Denis Villenueve's 'Dune' |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr |date=February 14, 2019 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/uncategorized/jason-momoa-dune-reboot-legendary-1203140272/ |title=Jason Momoa Joins Timothee Chalamet, Javier Bardem in 'Dune' Reboot |first=Justin |last=Kroll |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=February 14, 2019 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2020, Momoa appeared in a half time commercial for Rocket Mortgage for Superbowl 54. He also appeared in the teaser for \"Scary Little Green Men\" by [[Ozzy Osbourne]] from his album [[Ordinary Man (Ozzy Osbourne album)|Ordinary Man]].\n\n==Personal life==\n[[File:Jason Momoa by Gage Skidmore.jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|Momoa in July 2017]]\nMomoa began a relationship with actress [[Lisa Bonet]] in 2005.<ref name=\"horse\">{{cite news |url=https://abc7.com/archive/8318234/ |title=Jason Momoa of 'Conan the Barbarian' talks about his horse fears |date=August 20, 2011 |first=Olivia |last=Allin |work=OnTheRedCarpet.com |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> Although it was previously believed that Momoa and Bonet married on November 15, 2007, the couple did not legally marry until October 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/jason-momoa-lisa-bonet-officially-marry-in-secret-wedding/ |title=Jason Momoa and Lisa Bonet Just Got Officially Married: Details on Their Secret Wedding |date=November 2, 2017 |work=Us Weekly |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> Through his marriage to Bonet, Momoa is the stepfather to [[Zo\u00eb Kravitz]]. In July 2007, Bonet gave birth to their first child, a daughter.<ref name=\"horse\"/> Their second child, a son, was born in December 2008.<ref>{{cite web |date=January 9, 2009 |url=https://www.today.com/popculture/lisa-bonets-new-babys-name-mouthful-wbna28584888 |title=Lisa Bonet's New Baby's Name Is a Mouthful |work=[[Access Hollywood]] |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMomoa learned martial arts for his role as Ronon in ''Stargate Atlantis''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://stargate.mgm.com/view/content/1418/ |title=Jason Momoa on Martial Arts |date=August 14, 2009 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304051021/http://stargate.mgm.com/view/content/1418/ |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> and for ''Conan''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.starpulse.com/Actors/Momoa,_Jason/Biography/ |title=Jason Momoa Biography |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304043004/http://www.starpulse.com/Actors/Momoa,_Jason/Biography/ |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> In 2017, Momoa started practicing [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Jason Momoa Trains Jiu-Jitsu |url=https://www.bjjee.com/articles/jason-momoa-trains-jiu-jitsu/ |website=BJJEE |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Jason Momoa's Instagram post |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BQhSoriBswN/ |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> Momoa has also practiced proper screaming technique with Oli Peters, the vocalist of [[technical death metal]] band [[Archspire]] for a war cry scene in ''[[See (TV series)|See]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.revolvermag.com/culture/jason-momoa-trained-archspire-vocalist-learn-war-cry-see/|title=Jason Momoa Trained with Archspire Vocalist to Learn War Cry for 'See'|date=November 19, 2019|website=Revolver}}</ref>\n\nHe has multiple tattoos. The most notable tattoo is a halfsleeve on his left forearm, which is a tribute to his family god, or \u201c[[aumakua]]\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a22515826/jason-momoa-aquaman-tattoos/|title=Are Jason Momoa's 'Aquaman' Tattoos Actually Real?|last=Friedman|first=Megan|date=2018-07-23|website=Men's Health|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-24}}</ref> He is a fan of [[heavy metal music]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metalsucks.net/2019/06/13/actor-jason-momoa-hung-out-with-slayer-and-anthrax/|title=Actor Jason Momoa Hung Out with Slayer and Anthrax|date=June 13, 2019|website=MetalSucks}}</ref> and has noted that he \"build[s] [his] characters off of metal songs\";<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metalsucks.net/2018/12/11/jason-momoa-drew-inspiration-for-playing-aquaman-from-metallica-black-sabbath-and-tool/|title=Jason Momoa Drew Inspiration for Playing Aquaman from Metallica, Black Sabbath, and Tool &#124; MetalSucks|date=December 11, 2018|via=www.metalsucks.net}}</ref> he has invited members of [[Archspire]] to appear in cameos in the first episode of ''[[See (TV series)|See]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metalsucks.net/2019/11/02/jason-momoa-recruits-archspire-members-for-new-apple-tv-show/|title=Jason Momoa Recruits Archspire Members for New Apple TV+ Show &#124; MetalSucks|date=November 2, 2019|via=www.metalsucks.net}}</ref>\n\nMomoa is noted for having a close friendship with [[Emilia Clarke]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/emilia-clarkes-birthday-post-for-jason-momoa-will-make-you-cherish-their-friendship-more-18367274|title=Emilia Clark's Birthday Post For Jason Momoa Will Make You Cherish Their Friendship More|website=Elite Daily|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=October 29|first=Julie Scagell|title=Jason Momoa And Emilia Clarke's Genuine Friendship Is The Content We Need RN|date=2019-10-29|url=https://www.scarymommy.com/jason-momoa-emilia-clarke-graham-norton-show/|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20|last2=2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thethings.com/15-sweet-things-to-know-about-jason-momoa-and-emilia-clarkes-friendship/|title=15 Sweet Things To Know About Jason Momoa And Emilia Clarke's Friendship|date=2020-02-11|website=TheThings|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\n===Facial scar===\nOn November 15, 2008, Momoa was slashed in the face with a broken beer glass by a man during an altercation at the Birds Cafe, a tavern in [[Hollywood, California]].<ref name=\"NBC1\">{{cite web |title=Man Pleads Not Guilty To Assaulting \"Stargate Atlantis\" Actor |url=https://www.nbclosangeles.com/entertainment/celebrity/Man-Pleads-Not-Guilty-to-Assaulting-Stargate-Atlantis-Actor.html |publisher=[[KNBC]] |date=July 17, 2009 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"latimes\">{{cite web |url=https://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2009/10/5year-sentence-for-man-who-attacked-stargate-atalantis-actor-who-required-140-stitches.html |title=Five-year sentence for man who attacked 'Stargate Atlantis' actor Jason Momoa |last=Winton |first=Richard |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=October 7, 2009 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> He received approximately 140&nbsp;stitches during [[reconstructive surgery]] and the scar is apparent in his later work.<ref name=\"NBC1\"/> The assailant was sentenced to five years in prison for the attack.<ref name=\"latimes\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n<!--TV movies go in with the 'Television' section as per WP:FILMOGRAPHY \u2013 do NOT add here -->\n<!--Organize table in terms of domestic and/or international theatrical/VOD release date; festival premiere is not a release date -->\n<!-- Please note: do NOT use \"rowspans\" per WP:FILMOGRAPHY -->\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n!scope=\"col\"| Title\n!scope=\"col\"| Year\n!scope=\"col\"| Role\n!scope=\"col\"| Director\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Johnson Family Vacation]]''\n| 2004\n| Navarro\n| {{sort|Erskin|[[Christopher Erskin]]}}\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Pipeline (film)|Pipeline]]''\n| 2007\n| Kai\n| {{sort|Alan|Jordan Alan}}\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Conan the Barbarian (2011 film)|Conan the Barbarian]]''\n| 2011\n| [[Conan the Barbarian|Conan]]\n| {{sort|Nispel|[[Marcus Nispel]]}}\n| [[National Association of Theatre Owners|CinemaCon Award for Male Rising Star]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Bullet to the Head]]''\n| 2012\n| Keegan\n| {{sort|Hill|[[Walter Hill (director)|Walter Hill]]}}\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Road to Paloma]]''\n| rowspan=3|2014\n| {{sort|Wolf|Robert Wolf}}\n| Himself\n| Also director, producer and co-writer\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"collider\" />\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Debug (film)|Debug]]''\n| Iam\n| {{sort|Hewlett|[[David Hewlett]]}}\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Wolves (2014 film)|Wolves]]''\n| Connor\n| {{sort|Hayter|[[David Hayter]]}}\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]''\n| rowspan=2|2016\n| {{sort|Aquaman|[[Aquaman|Arthur Curry / Aquaman]]}}\n| {{sort|Snyder|[[Zack Snyder]]}}\n|Cameo\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"aquabat\"/>\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Sugar Mountain (film)|Sugar Mountain]]''\n| {{sort|Bright|Joe Bright}}\n| {{sort|Gray|[[Richard Gray (director)|Richard Gray]]}}\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"sugarmountain\"/>\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Once Upon a Time in Venice]]'' \n| rowspan=3|2017\n| Spyder\n| {{sort|Cullen|[[Mark and Robb Cullen]]}}\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |last=Kit |first=Borys |title=Jason Momoa, Thomas Middleditch and Famke Janssen Join Bruce Willis in Action Comedy (Exclusive) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jason-momoa-thomas-middleditch-famke-802754 |access-date=February 23, 2019 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=June 16, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row| ''{{sort|Bad|[[The Bad Batch]]}}''\n| {{sort|Man|Miami Man}}\n| {{sort|[[Amirpour]]|[[Ana Lily Amirpour]]}}\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"thebadbatch\"/>\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Justice League (film)|Justice League]]''\n| Arthur Curry / Aquaman\n| Zack Snyder\n| \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Braven]]''\n|rowspan=2|2018\n| Joe Braven\n| {{sort|Oeding|[[Lin Oeding]]}}\n| Also producer\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]''\n| Arthur Curry / Aquaman\n| {{sort|Wan|[[James Wan]]}}\n| Nominated - [[Kids' Choice Award|Kids' Choice Award for Favorite Movie Actor]]<br>Nominated - [[Kids' Choice Award|Kids' Choice Award for Favorite Superhero]]<br>Nominated - [[MTV Movie Award for Best Kiss]] <small>(shared with [[Amber Heard]])</small><br>Nominated - [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Actor \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Teen Choice Award for Choice Sci-Fi/Fantasy Movie Actor]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[The Lego Movie 2: The Second Part]]''\n| 2019\n| Aquaman\n| {{sort|Mitchell|[[Mike Mitchell (director)|Mike Mitchell]]}}\n| Voice\n|style=\"text-alig